President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the state of Maryland in response to the damages caused by Hurricane Irene from August 24 to September 5, 2011. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of facilities damaged by the hurricane in various counties in Maryland. Additionally, federal funding will be provided for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Regis Leo Phelan has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made based on the results of damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.